name: XL bully
summary: Tragic news has emerged regarding a series of incidents involving XL Bully dogs. In Lancashire, England, a man lost his life after being mauled by his XL Bully. The dog was subsequently shot and killed by police to ensure public safety. Similar events have occurred in Accrington and elsewhere in England and Wales, leading to the deaths of several individuals and the euthanization of hundreds of XL Bullies. These incidents have raised concerns among residents and animal welfare advocates, with campaigners securing legal approval to challenge the ban on XL Bullies. The authorities have emphasized the importance of responsible dog ownership and the potential danger posed by certain breeds like XL Bullies.

name: Ian McKellen
summary: Acclaimed actor Sir Ian McKellen, 85, has expressed his gratitude for a fat suit that he believes saved him from a serious injury during a stage fall at a West End show. McKellen, who was performing in the title role of "King Lear," fell backward during the curtain call and was hospitalized for two weeks. In interviews, McKellen has described the fall as a "horrible" experience but credited the fat suit he wore as Falstaff in "The Merry Wives of Windsor" with cushioning the blow and preventing more severe damage. While McKellen is still recovering from the fall and has experienced some psychological effects, such as anxiety and a fear of going out, he is grateful for his escape from a potentially life-threatening incident.
